WEBVTT

00:00.031 --> 00:02.906
LAINEY: <i>Back in the '90s,
school plays were all the rage.</i>

00:02.984 --> 00:04.265
<i>You had nervous auditions,</i>

00:04.336 --> 00:06.803
<i>all the drama of drama rehearsals,</i>

00:06.838 --> 00:09.906
<i>and the intoxicating glory
of show night.</i>

00:09.975 --> 00:12.391
<i>Last year, my big triumph was "Rent."</i>

00:12.461 --> 00:14.144
<i>It was a huge success.</i>

00:14.212 --> 00:16.023
<i>I didn't know if I could ever top it,</i>

00:16.094 --> 00:17.984
<i>but maybe I didn't have to.</i>

00:18.063 --> 00:19.896
Okay, guys. I know
there's been a lot of buzz

00:19.931 --> 00:21.798
about the show I'm picking
for this year's musical.

00:21.867 --> 00:23.767
Obviously, there are huge expectations,

00:23.802 --> 00:25.602
given that we crushed it
last year with "Rent."

00:25.670 --> 00:27.170
Best night of my life!

00:27.239 --> 00:29.105
My grandma said we were better
than Broadway.

00:29.174 --> 00:32.509
Exactly. Everyone is expecting
us to go bigger and better.

00:32.577 --> 00:34.411
I think I have the perfect show in mind.

00:34.513 --> 00:35.812
How about "Miss Saigon"?

00:35.881 --> 00:37.816
We can land an actual helicopter

00:37.863 --> 00:39.349
onstage like they do on Broadway.

00:39.418 --> 00:41.584
Yeah. You're right. We could go bigger,

00:41.653 --> 00:44.120
or we could do this!

00:44.222 --> 00:45.422
"Paint Your Wagon."

00:45.490 --> 00:47.557
- What?!
- It's a musical classic.

00:47.592 --> 00:51.060
It's about this wagon,
and it needs, like, painting.

00:51.129 --> 00:52.462
So they paint it.

00:52.531 --> 00:54.230
And then they sing
about having painted it.

00:54.299 --> 00:55.865
And don't get me started
on the awesome songs.

00:55.934 --> 00:57.133
♪ Paint your wagon ♪

00:57.235 --> 00:58.468
♪ Don't forget your brush ♪

00:58.537 --> 01:00.069
♪ Hope you brought some primer ♪

01:00.172 --> 01:01.905
♪ Then you paint it orange ♪

01:01.973 --> 01:03.139
Have you even seen it?

01:03.208 --> 01:04.674
Not yet. I'm going off the title.

01:04.742 --> 01:06.810
I've been looking forward
to this for a year.

01:06.878 --> 01:08.478
Figured we'd do something big again.

01:08.547 --> 01:11.214
No, we've gotta give people
what they're not expecting.

01:11.316 --> 01:12.415
They zig, we zag!

01:12.484 --> 01:14.384
They want a helicopter,
we give 'em a wagon!

01:14.453 --> 01:15.985
And guess what that wagon needs?

01:16.054 --> 01:17.420
TOGETHER: [Flatly] Paint.

01:17.489 --> 01:20.089
That's the spirit! Go, wagons!

01:20.192 --> 01:21.424
♪ Don't forget your primer ♪

01:21.526 --> 01:23.092
♪ Then you paint it orange ♪

01:23.161 --> 01:25.895
♪ One of these days,
you're gonna get outta here ♪

01:25.997 --> 01:28.898
♪ Live your life and finally be free ♪

01:29.000 --> 01:31.901
♪ Go where you wanna go,
do what you wanna do ♪

01:32.003 --> 01:35.571
♪ Someday, you will say
"Those were the days" ♪

01:35.633 --> 01:37.807
<i>It was November 6, 1990-something,</i>

01:37.909 --> 01:39.976
<i>and Coach was doing
what he did best... coaching.</i>

01:40.078 --> 01:41.377
<i>But that wasn't his only legacy.</i>

01:41.480 --> 01:43.213
<i>Back when he was a student
at our school,</i>

01:43.315 --> 01:45.782
<i>Rick Mellor set a ton of sports records,</i>

01:45.884 --> 01:46.983
<i>but not for much longer.</i>

01:47.085 --> 01:49.152
Never thought I'd see the day
when my record

01:49.254 --> 01:51.221
for most interceptions in a game
would get shattered.

01:51.323 --> 01:53.223
This Matt Ryan kid's
got mad skills, dude.

01:53.325 --> 01:54.891
Eh, break one of my records, sure.

01:54.993 --> 01:57.093
But I still got eight more
that are untouchable.

01:57.195 --> 01:58.628
<i>Oh, they were very touchable.</i>

01:58.730 --> 02:00.430
<i>His longest field goal record,</i>

02:00.532 --> 02:02.365
<i>his most dunks record,</i>

02:02.434 --> 02:04.000
<i>his fastest pin record.</i>

02:04.102 --> 02:06.035
Bro, look. You're off the whole board.

02:06.104 --> 02:07.237
Did not see that coming.

02:07.339 --> 02:08.404
Need a hug, dude?

02:08.507 --> 02:10.707
Not at all.
'Cause at the end of the day,

02:10.809 --> 02:12.742
I will always have one record
that will never be beat

02:12.844 --> 02:15.411
in a sporting event so bizarre,

02:15.514 --> 02:18.414
so dangerous, so all-around stupid

02:18.517 --> 02:21.117
that most people won't even go near it.

02:21.219 --> 02:22.318
The pole vault!

02:22.420 --> 02:23.987
♪

02:24.089 --> 02:25.522
It's just so random.

02:25.624 --> 02:27.390
Aside from Johnny Kittredge here,

02:27.492 --> 02:29.492
nobody will touch that pole
with a 10-foot pole.

02:29.561 --> 02:32.262
[Grunts]

02:32.364 --> 02:33.596
Then how'd you set the record?

02:33.698 --> 02:35.298
It was my senior year.

02:35.400 --> 02:38.434
Our only vaulter took a pole
to the tush.

02:38.537 --> 02:39.969
Coach needed a sub.

02:40.071 --> 02:41.571
Naturally, he called upon me,

02:41.640 --> 02:43.239
being that I'm the perfect specimen

02:43.341 --> 02:45.675
and built for excellence in all sports.

02:45.777 --> 02:47.844
His words, not mine.

02:47.946 --> 02:51.214
Without hesitation, I grabbed
that giant, wobbly pole,

02:51.316 --> 02:53.216
and I launched myself skyward,

02:53.285 --> 02:57.554
elegantly soaring
14 feet, 7 inches over that bar,

02:57.622 --> 02:59.322
shattering the school record for all...

02:59.424 --> 03:00.823
Oh, you did it!

03:00.926 --> 03:02.825
Oh, sweet Lord, no!

03:02.928 --> 03:04.994
14 feet, 2 inches!

03:05.096 --> 03:06.729
- Attaboy, Tory!
- Thanks, Coach K!

03:06.831 --> 03:08.398
14 feet, 2 inches?

03:08.500 --> 03:09.999
That new kid's
dangerously close to your...

03:10.101 --> 03:11.334
I'm fully aware of how close he is.

03:11.436 --> 03:12.602
So whatcha gonna do?

03:12.671 --> 03:14.304
There's nothing to do.

03:14.406 --> 03:16.105
As a coach, it's my job to make sure

03:16.199 --> 03:18.314
these kids achieve excellence
no matter what they try...

03:18.392 --> 03:21.244
Oh, crap, he's going again?

03:21.346 --> 03:22.412
[Whistle blows]

03:22.447 --> 03:23.479
[Body thuds]

03:23.548 --> 03:25.181
Oops! My bad! Sorry!

03:25.283 --> 03:26.649
Whistle got away from me.

03:26.718 --> 03:28.851
<i>While Mellor was lowering
the bar on the field,</i>

03:28.920 --> 03:30.620
<i>I was lowering the bar for myself.</i>

03:30.722 --> 03:33.056
Oh, boy! "Paint Your Wagon"!

03:33.158 --> 03:34.490
May I?

03:34.593 --> 03:36.125
Annnnd garbage.

03:36.194 --> 03:38.628
Hey! It took me almost a minute
to make those!

03:38.697 --> 03:40.196
I heard about your baffling choice

03:40.231 --> 03:41.664
for the fall musical, Ms. Lewis.

03:41.766 --> 03:42.765
It's not happening.

03:42.834 --> 03:46.135
You are doing this... "The Lion King."

03:46.237 --> 03:47.236
"The Lion King"?

03:47.339 --> 03:48.638
"The Lion King"?!

03:48.707 --> 03:50.073
Wilma, we're doing "The Lion King."

03:50.175 --> 03:52.308
- Yeah, I've been here for all of it.
- Oh, my God.

03:52.344 --> 03:54.377
This is, no joke,
my favorite movie-musical

03:54.479 --> 03:56.346
turned musical-musical ever.

03:56.448 --> 03:59.315
♪ The circle of life ♪

04:00.352 --> 04:02.685
- The... The lettuce is the little cub.
- Yeah, we got it.

04:02.787 --> 04:04.287
Earl, you do know "The Lion King"

04:04.389 --> 04:07.056
is a hit Broadway show with a huge cast,

04:07.158 --> 04:08.925
big numbers, awesome costumes.

04:08.994 --> 04:11.361
There's also a stampede
of angry wildebeests onstage.

04:11.429 --> 04:12.962
Simba doesn't get tackled, fortunately,

04:13.031 --> 04:14.897
but some heavy adult themes sure do.

04:14.966 --> 04:18.166
Lainey, this play
is the hottest ticket this year,

04:18.269 --> 04:19.469
thanks to you.

04:19.536 --> 04:21.603
I've got the Philly Post
coming, alumni flying in.

04:21.673 --> 04:23.906
Even Sir Elton John is coming.

04:24.009 --> 04:25.141
- What?!
- BOTH: What?!

04:25.210 --> 04:27.777
Well, I left word
with his agent's assistant,

04:27.812 --> 04:29.379
who hung up, but that's not a no.

04:29.481 --> 04:31.848
Well, Wilm 'n I think Sir Elton's a fool

04:31.916 --> 04:33.282
if he misses this show.

04:33.351 --> 04:34.917
[Chuckles]
Yeah, we're not a team on this.

04:34.986 --> 04:36.152
Good luck, Ms. Lewis.

04:36.221 --> 04:38.621
And I have no doubt
you'll make it just as thrilling

04:38.690 --> 04:40.323
as the million-dollar Disney production

04:40.392 --> 04:41.924
in the heart of Times Square.

04:41.993 --> 04:44.894
<i>While Ball threw a wrench in my plans,</i>

04:44.929 --> 04:46.929
<i>Mellor was trying to throw
a wrench of his own.</i>

04:47.032 --> 04:49.565
John, can I talk to you for a second?

04:49.634 --> 04:50.967
It's super important.

04:51.036 --> 04:53.536
I'd like to help Katman
with the boy's track team,

04:53.605 --> 04:54.604
if that's okay with you.

04:54.706 --> 04:55.638
Wow.

04:55.674 --> 04:57.373
That's incredibly generous of you, Rick.

04:57.442 --> 04:59.108
Well, it's just me helping where I can

04:59.177 --> 05:01.144
and certainly has nothing to do
with a personal agenda.

05:01.212 --> 05:02.712
Don't know why you'd make
that clarification,

05:02.814 --> 05:03.713
but thank you.

05:03.815 --> 05:05.181
You truly are selfless, Rick.

05:05.283 --> 05:07.417
Hey, that's your new nickname...
Selfless Rick.

05:07.452 --> 05:08.818
I don't do it for the nicknames, John.

05:08.920 --> 05:11.154
Okay, Modest Rick. [Chuckles]

05:11.222 --> 05:12.588
No. I'm gonna keep working on it.

05:12.657 --> 05:14.157
Modest Rick is not cutting it.

05:14.225 --> 05:16.059
But you are definitely gonna
get a new nickname.

05:16.127 --> 05:18.961
All that matters to me is I do
what's best for these kids.

05:18.997 --> 05:20.163
Tory, you're out.

05:20.231 --> 05:22.065
- No more pole vaulting for you.
- Why?

05:22.167 --> 05:25.168
It's time you follow
your true passion...

05:25.270 --> 05:26.869
the hammer throw.

05:26.971 --> 05:28.004
What's that thing?

05:28.073 --> 05:29.405
It's a hammer that you throw.

05:29.507 --> 05:31.374
How do you not know this?
It's your passion.

05:31.476 --> 05:33.309
Hey, Rick's back.

05:33.411 --> 05:36.212
To what do we owe this pleasure, pal?

05:36.281 --> 05:38.047
Glascott asked me to give you a hand,

05:38.116 --> 05:40.717
so I'm making some bold moves
to fix this broken team.

05:40.819 --> 05:42.218
Oh, man, that's great.

05:42.287 --> 05:43.986
Glad I got your trust, partner.

05:44.055 --> 05:45.254
All right, Tory, have at it!

05:49.160 --> 05:50.860
[Glass shatters]

05:50.962 --> 05:52.995
We did good work here today.

05:53.064 --> 05:54.797
<i>While Katman was none the wiser,</i>

05:54.899 --> 05:56.466
<i>Glascott was onto Mellor.</i>

05:56.534 --> 05:58.301
Hey-hey! Got a message
the big boss-man wanted to

05:58.369 --> 06:00.069
see good ol' Selfless Rick!

06:00.138 --> 06:03.005
More like Selfish Rick.
You got Tory throwing hammers?

06:03.074 --> 06:05.908
So what's this all about?
Some stupid sports record?

06:06.010 --> 06:07.910
Stupid? Those records are my legacy.

06:07.979 --> 06:10.079
Rick, you're one of
the top coaches in the city.

06:10.148 --> 06:12.115
Maybe it's time to move on
from that wall.

06:12.217 --> 06:13.916
Oh, you are such a hypocrite.

06:13.985 --> 06:15.251
- Excuse me?
- Don't act like you don't care

06:15.320 --> 06:16.619
about awards and accolades.

06:16.721 --> 06:18.354
You display yours for all to see!

06:18.423 --> 06:19.989
I worked my butt off for those.

06:20.091 --> 06:21.190
So did I! How would you feel

06:21.292 --> 06:22.925
if my name replaced yours on this wall?

06:22.994 --> 06:24.160
That's not even possible.

06:24.229 --> 06:25.161
Is that a challenge?

06:25.230 --> 06:26.429
No. It's the reality.

06:26.498 --> 06:28.431
Then it's settled!
I will stop at nothing

06:28.500 --> 06:30.733
until I surpass everything
you've ever accomplished,

06:30.802 --> 06:32.034
starting with...

06:32.137 --> 06:35.471
graduating with honors
from Howard University!

06:35.573 --> 06:37.840
- You really won't.
- Oh, I'm going.

06:37.876 --> 06:40.409
And you think you're so special
because you got a 4.0?

06:40.478 --> 06:42.912
- Mm-hmm.
- I'll double it and get an 8.0.

06:42.981 --> 06:44.313
They don't give those, I think.

06:44.382 --> 06:45.314
They won't have a choice.

06:45.350 --> 06:46.883
And when I am named valedictorian,

06:46.985 --> 06:48.351
I'll give a commencement speech

06:48.419 --> 06:50.620
declaring that Rick Mellor
is far superior

06:50.722 --> 06:52.021
than John Glascott

06:52.090 --> 06:54.223
and every single student
at Howard University.

06:54.292 --> 06:56.692
Okay, I know we're fighting,
but, really, don't do that.

06:56.761 --> 06:59.962
Next, I'll win each
and every award you've ever won,

07:00.064 --> 07:02.331
not just once, but multiple times.

07:02.400 --> 07:05.334
Really? You're gonna win
the Quaker Head of School Award

07:05.403 --> 07:06.669
without even being principal?

07:06.771 --> 07:08.504
I'll become one and win six!

07:08.606 --> 07:09.772
And for my coup de grace,

07:09.874 --> 07:12.909
I will become
the rightful owner of this.

07:13.011 --> 07:15.611
My #1 Uncle mug that Felicia gave me?

07:15.680 --> 07:16.779
You're not even her uncle!

07:16.888 --> 07:18.588
Yet! I shall wine and dine

07:18.650 --> 07:21.083
and ultimately wed
your older sister, Claire,

07:21.119 --> 07:23.820
aunt of Felicia Glascott,
your pride and joy.

07:23.888 --> 07:24.987
Doesn't matter.

07:25.089 --> 07:27.323
I'm Felicia's rock, always have been!

07:27.392 --> 07:28.524
Until now!

07:28.626 --> 07:30.593
My life's mission is
to lavish Felicia with love,

07:30.695 --> 07:32.762
support, and mall shopping sprees

07:32.831 --> 07:34.230
until this mug is mine!

07:34.332 --> 07:35.898
That's hurtful, Rick!

07:36.000 --> 07:37.533
In fact, I have a new nickname for you.

07:37.635 --> 07:38.835
It's Hurtful Rick!

07:38.903 --> 07:40.503
Well, soon enough
you're gonna be calling me

07:40.538 --> 07:43.239
"All of John's Greatest Achievements
Have Been Taken by Me" Rick.

07:43.308 --> 07:44.273
How's that sound?

07:44.375 --> 07:45.875
I think it's long and clunky.

07:45.977 --> 07:47.310
Then coming up with a better nickname

07:47.378 --> 07:48.477
will be my first task!

07:48.546 --> 07:51.280
My #1 Uncle mug handle.

07:51.382 --> 07:52.748
Look what you've done!

07:52.851 --> 07:53.816
Now it's just a cup.

07:53.918 --> 07:55.117
First I'll fix this mug.

07:55.220 --> 07:56.452
Then I'll marry your sister.

07:56.554 --> 07:57.720
[Groans]

07:57.789 --> 07:59.455
<i>While Mellor was protecting his legacy,</i>

07:59.524 --> 08:01.123
<i>I was researching "The Lion King"</i>

08:01.192 --> 08:02.825
<i>and thinking my own legacy was about to</i>

08:02.927 --> 08:05.328
<i>go down the drain.</i>

08:05.396 --> 08:06.462
I can't do this play.

08:06.564 --> 08:08.431
Oh, come on. Last year
you fought so hard

08:08.533 --> 08:09.465
to get a big play.

08:09.567 --> 08:10.700
Now they're letting you do the biggest.

08:10.802 --> 08:11.868
Exactly.

08:11.936 --> 08:13.336
There's gonna be
all these huge expectations.

08:13.438 --> 08:15.371
- That's not my thing.
- Expectations?

08:15.473 --> 08:17.340
As in having someone
think so highly of you

08:17.442 --> 08:19.609
that they assume everything
you do will be amazing?

08:19.711 --> 08:21.677
Yes. It is messed up, man.

08:21.779 --> 08:22.845
When I was a student here,

08:22.947 --> 08:24.480
I meticulously arranged my life

08:24.549 --> 08:26.494
so that no one would
expect anything of me.

08:26.519 --> 08:27.527
That sounds like a lot of work

08:27.552 --> 08:28.784
to get the result of nothing.

08:28.830 --> 08:29.861
But worth it.

08:29.921 --> 08:31.254
My teachers didn't care how I did.

08:31.356 --> 08:32.722
They were just impressed I came to class

08:32.823 --> 08:34.357
instead of siphoning gas
out of their cars.

08:34.458 --> 08:36.392
But now you're a grown-up
with an actual job,

08:36.494 --> 08:39.595
which means actual people
expect you to do actual things.

08:39.664 --> 08:41.597
But I've already done a ton
of great stuff here,

08:41.698 --> 08:43.599
and I just keep getting
asked for more and more.

08:43.668 --> 08:45.301
When can I be like, "We're cool, right?"

08:45.403 --> 08:46.736
Seeing that it's your job, never.

08:46.838 --> 08:49.872
But stop freaking out. We can help you.

08:49.974 --> 08:51.107
Oh, my God, yeah. Let me help.

08:51.209 --> 08:52.408
I know every word to "The Lion King."

08:52.510 --> 08:54.644
I can also help the kids
with the lyrics and the lines.

08:54.746 --> 08:56.345
I'm really good at animal sounds.

08:56.447 --> 08:57.923
Here's an example. Here's a Shih Tzu.

08:57.993 --> 08:59.849
- [Barks]
- And I can show the kids

08:59.951 --> 09:01.450
how to sew some amazing costumes.

09:01.524 --> 09:02.485
Really?

09:02.517 --> 09:04.060
In college, I had a side hustle

09:04.155 --> 09:05.721
making bootleg Beanie Babies.

09:05.823 --> 09:08.090
That's right. Wilma was a bad girl.

09:08.192 --> 09:09.525
Wow, thank you.

09:09.627 --> 09:11.193
Um, you can handle the costumes.

09:11.296 --> 09:13.863
- Me and CB will cover the auditions.
- Oh, man!

09:13.965 --> 09:15.064
I can't wait to teach our Timon

09:15.166 --> 09:17.400
how to do a perfect
Nathan Lane impression.

09:17.502 --> 09:19.568
[Bad Italian accent]
I-I'll-a tell ya, Simba.

09:19.671 --> 09:21.122
This a-stinks.

09:21.147 --> 09:22.148
[Normal voice] I'm sorry. I'm just...

09:22.173 --> 09:23.239
I'm overwhelmed, and I'm excited.

09:23.341 --> 09:24.707
Whoo! I'm gonna go practice.

09:24.809 --> 09:27.029
<i>It's official. I was screwed.</i>

09:28.029 --> 09:30.824
<i>The school had big expectations
for "The Lion King,"</i>

09:30.941 --> 09:33.642
<i>but judging by the auditions,
I was in big trouble.</i>

09:33.714 --> 09:35.398
Simba, I want to tell you something

09:35.453 --> 09:36.722
that my father told me.

09:36.791 --> 09:37.890
Sorry. Sorry to cut in.

09:37.958 --> 09:39.792
It's just, Mufasa's played
by James Earl Jones,

09:39.860 --> 09:41.440
so you gotta deepen the ol' voice box.

09:41.465 --> 09:42.478
How deep?

09:42.503 --> 09:45.190
Well, he also plays Darth Vader,
so mad deep.

09:45.299 --> 09:46.832
Vader. Got it.

09:46.934 --> 09:48.967
Simba! Krrrr-sshhh!

09:49.036 --> 09:51.503
I am your father! Krrrr...

09:51.605 --> 09:53.238
- Thank you for your time.
- We'll be in touch.

09:53.340 --> 09:54.773
[Chuckles]

09:54.842 --> 09:56.842
Wow. Who knew finding James Earl Jones

09:56.911 --> 09:58.510
in a Quaker middle school
would be so hard?

09:58.605 --> 09:59.611
Oh, wait, I did!

09:59.699 --> 10:00.712
I know you're worried, Lains,

10:00.781 --> 10:03.115
but just like the song says,
hakuna matata.

10:03.144 --> 10:04.126
Screw the song.

10:04.151 --> 10:05.517
I've got nine male animals to cast

10:05.586 --> 10:06.885
and only three boys who have auditioned.

10:06.910 --> 10:07.963
Yeah, but the good news?

10:07.988 --> 10:09.555
- Hakuna matata.
- You're making it worse.

10:09.657 --> 10:11.023
Yeah, but you know
how I can make it better?

10:11.125 --> 10:12.825
- Say it with me.
- Hakuna-mama.

10:12.893 --> 10:15.060
- Say it with me. Come on.
- Hakuna-mama.

10:15.162 --> 10:16.528
Hakuna matata!

10:16.630 --> 10:19.431
No worries about the incredibly
marginal talent pool.

10:19.500 --> 10:22.134
The real star of "Lion King"...
the music.

10:22.203 --> 10:24.136
You know what? You're right.
It is about the music.

10:24.238 --> 10:28.240
[Instruments playing off-key]

10:28.342 --> 10:30.876
Wow, great work, everyone!

10:30.945 --> 10:32.945
When you're done warming up,
let's hear "Circle of Life."

10:33.047 --> 10:34.513
I believe that was "Circle of Life."

10:34.615 --> 10:36.982
- Oh, that's worrisome.
- No, no worries.

10:37.051 --> 10:39.218
'Cause even if our pit
is rough around the edges,

10:39.320 --> 10:41.887
the real reason why people
love "The Lion King"

10:41.989 --> 10:44.590
is the epic, life-size animal costumes.

10:44.658 --> 10:47.526
[Dramatic music playing]

10:47.595 --> 10:48.560
Ta-da!

10:48.662 --> 10:50.429
Gah! What the hell am I looking at?!

10:50.531 --> 10:52.064
Here's our giraffe.

10:52.166 --> 10:54.566
Ha. We overshot the neck a bit.

10:54.635 --> 10:57.803
A bit? It looks like he was
just cut down from the gallows.

10:57.872 --> 10:59.738
Moving on, that's a zebra.

10:59.807 --> 11:03.208
It looks like it was murdered
and came back to seek revenge.

11:03.310 --> 11:05.811
And finally, we have
our majestic elephant.

11:05.880 --> 11:07.112
My measurements were a bit off,

11:07.181 --> 11:08.614
and we ran out of materials.

11:08.716 --> 11:10.549
Oh, God. It's like if the Elephant Man

11:10.618 --> 11:11.683
were an actual elephant.

11:11.785 --> 11:12.818
I'm sorry!

11:12.887 --> 11:14.353
I thought it was like sew a button here,

11:14.455 --> 11:15.454
glue some felt there!

11:15.522 --> 11:17.422
I'm the science teacher, not Bob Mackie!

11:17.524 --> 11:18.657
Everyone, it's fine.

11:18.726 --> 11:21.894
Let's just take a deep breath
and say hakuna ma...

11:21.962 --> 11:23.862
No. Don't you dare.
That song lied to us.

11:23.931 --> 11:25.931
No one should ever hakuna-matata
their way through life.

11:25.966 --> 11:29.034
But it's a problem-free
philosophy, remember?

11:29.103 --> 11:30.969
You don't see any problems
with the cast and crew

11:31.071 --> 11:32.504
and menagerie of jungle horrors?

11:32.606 --> 11:33.605
Well, yeah, part of me does.

11:33.674 --> 11:35.607
And then the other part's gonna go,

11:35.709 --> 11:37.676
"Hakuna matata, though, no worries."

11:37.778 --> 11:39.044
- Huh?
- Oh, I got worries.

11:39.113 --> 11:41.813
I got a lot of matata going on
in my body right now.

11:41.882 --> 11:43.282
- Where are you going?
- To fix this

11:43.384 --> 11:46.151
before I embarrass myself
and the entire school.

11:46.253 --> 11:48.587
Wait! Do you at least wanna see
the antelope we made?

11:48.689 --> 11:49.821
Ahhhhhhh!

11:49.857 --> 11:52.224
Holy [bleep], Wilma!

11:52.326 --> 11:54.092
<i>While my musical was falling apart,</i>

11:54.128 --> 11:56.995
<i>so was Mellor's plan to keep
his pole-vaulting record.</i>

11:57.064 --> 11:58.597
Whoa, whoa, whoa. What's all this?

11:58.699 --> 12:00.365
I'm a physics teacher, Rick.

12:00.467 --> 12:02.567
I'm using it to help Tory
improve his jump.

12:02.670 --> 12:03.936
You can't cheat with science.

12:04.038 --> 12:05.537
That's against the rules of sports.

12:05.572 --> 12:08.807
Buddy, Glascott made it clear
this is my team, not yours.

12:08.876 --> 12:10.475
Yeah? Well, he'll change his tune

12:10.544 --> 12:12.277
when I court and marry
his sister Claire.

12:12.346 --> 12:14.546
- [Chuckles]
- Please, just let it go.

12:14.615 --> 12:15.981
[Exhales sharply]

12:16.083 --> 12:18.850
Everyone in this school knows
you used to be a star athlete.

12:18.919 --> 12:20.218
Used to be?

12:20.287 --> 12:22.654
I could break my own record
right now if I so choose.

12:22.723 --> 12:24.389
- You really can't, pal.
- Says who?

12:24.491 --> 12:26.925
Says body mass, bone density,
lung capacity.

12:26.994 --> 12:29.695
Don't you dare diminish me
with your witch-like equations.

12:29.763 --> 12:31.863
I'll tell ya what.
If I go pole-vault right now

12:31.932 --> 12:33.832
and set a new record, it stands.

12:33.901 --> 12:37.336
And if you don't, you let it go
once and for all.

12:37.404 --> 12:38.370
What do ya say?

12:38.472 --> 12:41.406
I say prepare to witness greatness.

12:41.475 --> 12:43.408
It's Mellor Time.

12:43.510 --> 12:45.344
[Inspirational instrumental music plays]

12:45.446 --> 12:48.914
♪

12:49.016 --> 12:50.749
[Groaning]

12:50.851 --> 12:52.084
[Music stops]

12:52.186 --> 12:54.353
- Did I do it?
- Sure didn't, buddy,

12:54.421 --> 12:55.921
'cause, ya know, science.

12:55.990 --> 12:58.023
Ah, screw science. I'm going again.

12:58.125 --> 13:01.827
Okay, here I go! Uppsey daisy!

13:01.895 --> 13:03.495
LAINEY: Okay! [Claps hands]

13:03.597 --> 13:04.830
Listen up, everyone.

13:04.898 --> 13:07.232
Just want to say I am
so impressed with all of you.

13:07.334 --> 13:09.267
I mean, look at that set
our stage crew is building.

13:09.370 --> 13:12.104
Truly, you kids are insanely talented...

13:12.172 --> 13:14.239
which is why it was so hard
for me to hire adults

13:14.308 --> 13:15.507
who can do it all way better.

13:15.609 --> 13:16.641
Wait. What?

13:16.710 --> 13:18.210
My dad owns a tile and flooring company,

13:18.278 --> 13:20.412
so I borrowed a few workmen
to give us a little help

13:20.514 --> 13:21.613
in building every single thing.

13:21.715 --> 13:23.048
So what do we get to build?

13:23.117 --> 13:24.616
Camaraderie with your friends

13:24.651 --> 13:26.818
as you sit in the shadows
and watch the show come to life.

13:26.920 --> 13:29.154
Are you sure you don't want
the kids to help at all?

13:29.256 --> 13:31.456
Of course.
Just not the complicated stuff,

13:31.558 --> 13:33.925
like sets and costumes
and also the orchestra.

13:34.028 --> 13:37.329
Say hello to Pennsylvania's
third-best Rush cover band.

13:37.431 --> 13:38.630
You're gonna love what we did to the end

13:38.732 --> 13:40.232
of "I Just Can't Wait to Be King."

13:40.300 --> 13:41.533
Just stick to the sheet music.

13:41.635 --> 13:43.668
Okay, but if a good 10-hour
jam session happens,

13:43.771 --> 13:44.870
I can't fight it.

13:44.938 --> 13:47.773
Wow, lot of big changes.
What about the cast?

13:47.875 --> 13:49.041
You're all super stars,

13:49.143 --> 13:51.576
so just go up there
and have a great show.

13:51.645 --> 13:53.478
Minus the roles I've recast.

13:53.580 --> 13:54.646
You owe me big time.

13:54.715 --> 13:55.947
I'm missing a lot of work for this.

13:56.050 --> 13:57.382
And I'm missing the LSAT.

13:57.451 --> 14:00.285
It was either become a lawyer
or see my sweet Erica.

14:00.387 --> 14:01.453
Sup?

14:01.555 --> 14:02.721
You chose poorly.

14:02.823 --> 14:04.656
Meet our new Simba and Nala.

14:04.758 --> 14:05.791
- Why?!
- What?!

14:05.859 --> 14:07.459
Back in the day,
Dave Kim and Erica Goldberg

14:07.494 --> 14:09.027
were shining theater stars.

14:09.129 --> 14:10.095
Sorry, Jessica and Tom.

14:10.197 --> 14:11.730
You're also stars, just not as bright.

14:11.832 --> 14:12.731
But still stars.

14:12.800 --> 14:14.266
My grammy's coming from Portland.

14:14.368 --> 14:15.801
This is gonna be really hard to explain.

14:15.869 --> 14:18.103
I know you have a lot
of expectations on you, um,

14:18.205 --> 14:20.205
but the point of a student production

14:20.274 --> 14:22.340
is that it has actual students.

14:22.443 --> 14:25.944
Bummer. I was hoping you'd play
both Timon and Pumbaa.

14:26.046 --> 14:27.145
- Both?!
- You were saying?

14:27.247 --> 14:29.047
It's like someone
came up to me and said,

14:29.149 --> 14:30.449
"Your dream just came true,"

14:30.517 --> 14:31.883
and then some other guy was like,

14:31.985 --> 14:33.585
"Your other dream just came true."

14:33.687 --> 14:34.653
I'll take that as a yes.

14:34.721 --> 14:37.456
[Cockney accent] 'Allo! I'm Pumbaa!

14:37.558 --> 14:39.524
And I-I eat bugs, I do!

14:39.626 --> 14:40.992
Where are these accents coming from?

14:41.095 --> 14:43.295
Gah! I'm gonna work on it.

14:43.330 --> 14:45.831
Whoa, wait.
Where are you guys all going?

14:45.933 --> 14:48.300
We quit.
We didn't sign up to do nothing.

14:48.402 --> 14:50.102
I just wanted to put on
the best show possible.

14:50.204 --> 14:51.369
Without us.

14:51.405 --> 14:52.604
Doing theater with you
was supposed to be

14:52.706 --> 14:54.239
the best part of the whole school year.

14:54.308 --> 14:55.474
No, don't do that.

14:55.576 --> 14:57.576
I already have
so many expectations on me

14:57.678 --> 14:58.743
from Ball and everyone else.

14:58.812 --> 15:00.245
I can't have them from you guys, too.

15:00.347 --> 15:01.413
Last time I checked,

15:01.482 --> 15:03.715
we should be the only ones that matter.

15:03.817 --> 15:06.451
♪

15:06.520 --> 15:09.688
Cheggit, Dave Kim wears V-necks now.

15:09.790 --> 15:10.889
And guess how much I can bench.

15:10.991 --> 15:13.592
I don't know. Like 60 pounds?

15:13.694 --> 15:14.793
Yes.

15:14.895 --> 15:17.762
John, you got a sec for Hurtful Rick?

15:17.865 --> 15:20.265
Don't even. I just got off the
phone with my big sis, Claire.

15:20.367 --> 15:23.335
She said you asked her out
on a date to Planet Hollywood?

15:23.403 --> 15:25.403
- Don't worry.
- I will worry.

15:25.472 --> 15:28.140
Everyone knows it's the most
romantic restaurant in town,

15:28.242 --> 15:30.542
- after Rainforest Cafe.
- Calm down.

15:30.644 --> 15:32.844
Katman forced me to move on
from my old records

15:32.946 --> 15:34.379
and focus on the now.

15:34.448 --> 15:35.380
Really?

15:35.482 --> 15:38.016
Which is why I created a new board

15:38.085 --> 15:39.317
specifically for teachers.

15:39.386 --> 15:40.785
Teacher records?

15:40.888 --> 15:42.854
[Chuckles] Come on, Rick.
That's not a thing.

15:42.956 --> 15:43.889
Oh, but it is.

15:43.991 --> 15:45.257
There's a board, so it's official.

15:45.359 --> 15:46.892
But these records are insane.

15:46.994 --> 15:48.894
"Most Nerds Encouraged"?

15:48.996 --> 15:51.796
2,904 dweebs and counting.

15:51.899 --> 15:52.998
"Longest Whistle Blow"?

15:53.100 --> 15:55.901
18.2 seconds. You want to take me on?

15:56.003 --> 15:57.836
No. Most of these records
don't even apply

15:57.938 --> 15:59.337
to half the faculty.

15:59.439 --> 16:01.173
I mean, "Most High-Fives Delivered"?

16:01.275 --> 16:02.908
"Most Chicken Cubes Eaten"?

16:03.010 --> 16:04.442
"Thickest Right Calf"?

16:04.545 --> 16:06.545
"Most No-Handed Push-Ups"?

16:06.647 --> 16:07.679
How does that even work?

16:07.781 --> 16:08.813
It doesn't.

16:08.916 --> 16:11.016
I hurt myself real bad,
but I still did one.

16:11.118 --> 16:12.584
Okay, stop. There's no way
that I'm letting you

16:12.686 --> 16:14.019
hang this in the gym next to the kids

16:14.121 --> 16:15.387
who have worked so hard to get there.

16:15.489 --> 16:17.122
But I worked hard, too.

16:17.191 --> 16:19.925
That wall in the gym
is my crowning achievement.

16:20.027 --> 16:20.992
Now it's gone.

16:21.061 --> 16:22.594
Yeah, because you pushed those kids

16:22.696 --> 16:24.329
to be their best and to win.

16:24.431 --> 16:26.531
Exactly. They're the ones
who win, and not me.

16:26.633 --> 16:28.033
You don't get it, do you?

16:28.135 --> 16:30.869
The wall in your office
is full of achievements,

16:30.971 --> 16:32.737
and all my records are gone.

16:32.806 --> 16:34.773
My wall is blank.

16:36.263 --> 16:38.109
And it's gonna stay that way.

16:38.212 --> 16:42.113
♪

16:42.748 --> 16:44.649
<i>Thanks to my questionable directing,</i>

16:44.718 --> 16:46.009
<i>it was curtains for my production</i>

16:46.079 --> 16:48.134
- <i>of "The Lion King."</i>
- Whatcha up to, Lewis?

16:48.223 --> 16:49.856
I'm canceling the show.

16:49.925 --> 16:51.791
- You can't do that.
- It wasn't really my choice.

16:51.860 --> 16:53.526
All the kids I fired are quitting.

16:53.562 --> 16:54.861
Look, I know we all got swept away

16:54.930 --> 16:56.563
with this whole "Lion King" thing,

16:56.631 --> 16:59.332
and some of us may have spent
an entire month's salary

16:59.401 --> 17:01.067
- on a dialect coach.
- Did it help?

17:01.169 --> 17:03.036
[Jamaican accent] I'm Nathan Lane, mon.

17:03.105 --> 17:05.038
- Are you?
- [Normal voice] Obviously not.

17:05.073 --> 17:06.772
The point is all you wanted to do

17:06.875 --> 17:08.241
was put on a great show.

17:08.343 --> 17:09.608
It's a good thing.

17:09.711 --> 17:10.577
The hell it is.

17:10.679 --> 17:11.644
Life is so much easier

17:11.713 --> 17:13.213
when people expect nothing from you.

17:13.315 --> 17:15.348
Lainey, it's just a high school play.

17:15.450 --> 17:17.717
What's the worst that could
happen if it's not perfect?

17:17.752 --> 17:20.487
I embarrass myself and the kids
and this entire school.

17:20.589 --> 17:21.921
My response to that?

17:21.990 --> 17:23.056
Oh, no, what are you doing?

17:23.157 --> 17:24.057
[Piano music plays]

17:24.126 --> 17:26.192
♪ Hakuna matata ♪

17:26.294 --> 17:27.237
Don't do that.

17:27.262 --> 17:29.896
♪ What a wonderful phrase ♪

17:29.971 --> 17:30.901
Please stop.

17:30.966 --> 17:32.966
♪ Hakuna matata ♪

17:33.068 --> 17:34.033
You're making it worse.

17:34.136 --> 17:36.603
♪ Ain't no passing craze ♪

17:36.673 --> 17:39.405
- Are you done?
- ♪ It means no worries ♪

17:39.474 --> 17:42.942
♪ For the rest of your days ♪

17:43.044 --> 17:44.043
Holy crap, you can sing.

17:44.146 --> 17:46.446
♪ It's our problem-free ♪

17:46.515 --> 17:47.981
Why am I the music teacher?

17:48.049 --> 17:50.617
BOTH: ♪ Philosophy ♪

17:50.719 --> 17:51.818
Effortless harmonizing.

17:51.920 --> 17:53.019
♪ Hakuna ♪

17:53.121 --> 17:54.254
[Music stops]

17:56.525 --> 17:58.091
♪ Matata ♪

17:58.193 --> 17:59.592
There she is.

17:59.661 --> 18:00.760
[Laughs]

18:00.862 --> 18:02.328
Okay, I'm not giving up on this,

18:02.430 --> 18:03.663
but we got a lot of work to do.

18:03.732 --> 18:05.465
Wilma, go cancel the costumes I ordered

18:05.534 --> 18:07.400
- and fix up the old ones.
- Copy that.

18:07.502 --> 18:09.035
CB, tell Johnny Atkins and his band

18:09.137 --> 18:10.136
I've decided to part ways.

18:10.205 --> 18:11.704
Oh. That'll be fun.

18:11.773 --> 18:14.474
- Hey, CB?
- Yeah?

18:14.576 --> 18:18.444
You may be a terrible Timon
and an even worse Pumbaa...

18:18.547 --> 18:21.214
but you're an amazing guy.

18:21.283 --> 18:22.682
No worries.

18:22.751 --> 18:27.620
<i>♪ You should never
take more than you give ♪</i>

18:27.689 --> 18:32.692
<i>♪ In the circle of life ♪</i>

18:32.794 --> 18:33.860
Damn it!

18:33.962 --> 18:35.762
- You're hesitating.
- What?

18:35.830 --> 18:37.030
Stop thinking about your form

18:37.098 --> 18:38.665
and focus on getting over the bar.

18:38.767 --> 18:40.133
Rick, we had a deal.

18:40.235 --> 18:42.602
I know. I'm not here for me.

18:42.671 --> 18:44.671
I'm here to help him get that record.

18:44.773 --> 18:46.339
Stop doubting yourself.

18:46.408 --> 18:48.241
Back in the day,
I didn't have the best form,

18:48.343 --> 18:49.409
but I was fearless.

18:49.511 --> 18:50.743
You can do this.

18:50.812 --> 18:54.547
<i>♪ Till we find our place ♪</i>

18:54.649 --> 18:55.748
Go get it.

18:55.850 --> 19:01.821
<i>♪ On the path unwinding ♪</i>

19:01.923 --> 19:02.989
[Cheering]

19:03.091 --> 19:05.651
That's a new record, Rick.

19:05.729 --> 19:07.807
Big of you to let it go.

19:07.862 --> 19:09.948
- It just feels good to be a part of it.
<i>- ♪ The circle of life ♪</i>

19:10.026 --> 19:14.567
♪ Li-i-i-fe ♪

19:14.636 --> 19:16.493
<i>There's nothing scarier than when people</i>

19:16.555 --> 19:18.171
<i>have big expectations of you.</i>

19:18.240 --> 19:21.207
♪

19:21.309 --> 19:24.944
<i>But turns out, CB was right.</i>

19:25.046 --> 19:26.913
<i>I really didn't need to worry.</i>

19:27.015 --> 19:29.215
<i>That night, those parents watched</i>

19:29.317 --> 19:31.784
<i>the performance of a lifetime.</i>

19:31.886 --> 19:33.820
<i>Sure, it wasn't Broadway,</i>

19:33.922 --> 19:35.455
<i>but with my friends by my side,</i>

19:35.557 --> 19:37.790
<i>those kids were
able to reach new heights.</i>

19:37.859 --> 19:39.926
<i>'Cause in the end,</i>

19:39.995 --> 19:42.367
<i>that's the way
you'll be remembered forever.</i>

19:42.422 --> 19:45.632
<i>♪ In the circle ♪</i>

19:45.734 --> 19:48.434
Who cares about having
your name up on some wall

19:48.536 --> 19:50.903
when you can have it up
on the whole building?

19:51.006 --> 19:52.205
You did this?

19:52.307 --> 19:54.207
No, you did.

19:54.309 --> 19:56.909
And it wasn't by setting
all those records as a student.

19:57.012 --> 19:59.078
It was by being the best coach
these kids could have asked for

19:59.180 --> 20:00.546
for all these years.

20:00.649 --> 20:02.715
Thanks, John.

20:02.817 --> 20:05.218
I needed this win.

20:05.320 --> 20:07.020
- <i>♪ In the circle ♪</i>
- You've got plenty.

20:07.122 --> 20:10.123
- <i>♪ In the circle ♪</i>
- And you got plenty more in the future.

20:10.225 --> 20:15.061
<i>♪ The circle of life ♪</i>

20:15.163 --> 20:19.565
♪

20:20.310 --> 20:22.591
[Inhales sharply, exhales sharply]

20:22.707 --> 20:24.775
Come on! Just me like me
and Coach K taught you!

20:24.845 --> 20:27.809
Lead with your right!
You can do it, John Kittredge!

20:30.380 --> 20:32.544
- [Laughs]
- [Cheering]

20:32.739 --> 20:34.989
♪♪

20:35.060 --> 20:37.060
<font color="#0080ff">Synced & corrected by</font> kinglouisxx
<font color="#0080ff">www.</font>addic7ed<font color="#0080ff">.com</font>

20:38.622 --> 20:40.889
[Cheering]

20:40.991 --> 20:44.359
♪♪

20:44.420 --> 20:45.662
[Cheering]

20:45.725 --> 20:46.905
MAN: Nice.

20:46.980 --> 20:50.214
I cleared 10 feet on my first jump.

20:50.316 --> 20:52.250
- John...
- Didn't make it.

20:52.289 --> 20:54.554
...cleared it after
the competition was over.

20:54.579 --> 20:55.647
[Laughter]

20:55.672 --> 20:58.770
But let it be known,
John has jumped 10 feet.

20:58.795 --> 21:00.630
- Successfully.
- Officially.
